  "texts": [
    "The performances were represented using AUC values in predicting the experimentally validated new protein functions that were not included in CAFA4 data, and the performances of AnnoPRO, DeepGOPlus, NetGO3 and PFmulDL were highlighted in light red, light green, orange and light blue, respectively.",
    "For GO families in the 'Head Label Levels' (LEVEL 2 and LEVEL 3 provided in Additional file 1: Fig.",
    "S3), the performance of AnnoPRO was roughly as good as that of the other three methods (1.4 ~ 4.1% improvements in most cases, but 0.1% decline in one single case).",
    "For the GO families in the 'Tail Label Levels' (LEVEL 4 to LEVEL 10 shown in Additional file 1: Fig.",
    "S3), AnnoPRO demonstrated the consistently superior performance among four methods (1.7 ~ 28.2% improvements in all cases)."
  ],
